'''Charles B. "Charlie" Grandy''' is an American [[Stand-up comedy|stand-up comedian]], [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]] who has worked on series such as ''[[The Daily Show|The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]]'', ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|The Office]]'', ''[[Guys With Kids]]'', and ''[[The Mindy Project]]''. He is the son of former ''[[The Love Boat|Love Boat]]'' star turned politician [[Fred Grandy]].

== Career ==
After working as a stand-up comedian,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://comedians.jokes.com/charlie-grandy|title=Charlie Grandy: Stand Up Videos and Funny Clips|work=Jokes.com|accessdate=January 25, 2011}}</ref> Grandy turned to television writing and became a writer on [[Jon Stewart|Jon Stewart's]] ''The Daily Show'' in 2001. After his ''Daily Show'' stint, Grandy became a writer and producer on ''Saturday Night Live'', where he worked until 2008. In the same year, he joined the writing staff of the [[The Office (U.S. season 5)|fifth season]] of the American version of ''The Office''. At the beginning of the [[The Office (U.S. season 6)|sixth season]] he became a co-producer and by the time the show entered its [[The Office (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]], he had become a supervising producer of the series.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.film.com/celebrities/charlie-grandy/19169243|title=Charlie Grandy from The Office|work=Film.com|accessdate=January 25, 2011}}</ref> After the cancellation of his show, ''[[Guys With Kids]]'', he joined his former ''[[The Office (U.S. TV series)|Office]]'' cohort, [[Mindy Kaling]], on the second season of her show, ''[[The Mindy Project]]'', as a writer and co-executive producer.

